From 995e6fe3ef072972201601f196ac4c68cb56252d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Davanum Srinivas <davanum@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 11:27:47 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] test/integration/apiserver/discovery: allow slower
 cleanup in CI

The declarative discovery integration tests use a single 30 second timeout for APIService cleanup, CRD cleanup, and discovery convergence checks. On contended CI runners that budget is sometimes too short. The recent test-k8s failure in TestCRD/Race timed out while waiting for v1.stable.example.com to disappear during cleanup, even though the next rerun on the same SHA passed.

Increase the shared discovery test timeout to 60 seconds so the suite remains sensitive to real hangs, but no longer flakes on slow aggregator and API registration resync paths.

Tested:
- /opt/homebrew/bin/bash ./hack/verify-gofmt.sh
- /opt/homebrew/bin/bash ./hack/verify-typecheck.sh ./test/integration/apiserver/discovery/...
- go test ./test/integration/apiserver/discovery -run 'TestCRD/Race$' -count=10
---
 test/integration/apiserver/discovery/framework.go | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/test/integration/apiserver/discovery/framework.go b/test/integration/apiserver/discovery/framework.go
index bb335f885d7..d2d2d857bea 100644
--- a/test/integration/apiserver/discovery/framework.go
+++ b/test/integration/apiserver/discovery/framework.go
@@ -46,7 +46,9 @@ const acceptV1JSON = "application/json"
 const acceptV2JSON = "application/json;g=apidiscovery.k8s.io;v=v2;as=APIGroupDiscoveryList"
 const acceptV2JSONNoPeer = "application/json;g=apidiscovery.k8s.io;v=v2;as=APIGroupDiscoveryList;profile=nopeer"
 
-const maxTimeout = 30 * time.Second
+// Discovery integration tests frequently need to wait through aggregator and
+// API registration resync paths on contended CI nodes.
+const maxTimeout = 60 * time.Second
 
 type testClient interface {
 	kubernetes.Interface
